comment: Please see my photos of the terrible quality of this paper.  Every sheet in the reem is damaged/folded/scores/marked/bent.  It isn’t shipping damage, it is just how it was packaged from the factory.While the paper is the correct width, you can see all these strange folds that completely jam the printer.  They are in the package like that!

I was looking for a less expensive, quality paper I could use at home.  I have a Lexmark printer and usually use a way more expensive paper product.  I decided to give the Amazon paper a try.  This is what I found:  It was well packaged and arrived in good condition.  The thickness seems standard, not too thin.  Didn't really notice a bluish or grey tint.  For some reason, this paper seems to be very sensitive to humidity (I live in DC, which is generally very humid until fall/winter).  If left out, the edges of the paper will curl very slightly and even develop a ripple-like texture throughout a page due to humidity.  Because of this, the sheets will occasionally jam.  I have found that if I place the paper in the printer shortly before printing, this is not a problem.  This is because I keep my paper supply in a box and usually only print with "fresh" paper in the printer.  I only had two minor paper jams before I realized this.  I would NOT recommend this paper for high-output copiers, but only for home copiers, where you have humidity control and fewer copies.  Other than that, I find it to be serviceable and a very good value.  Based on price alone, I would probably purchase this paper again.

I ordered this paper as a cheaper option for my older home printer (Epsom 3540) that I typically use for basic home functions such as printing shipping labels, recipes, and other small tasks.  I've been through one package and the paper works great.  I don't notice a tinted blue color as other reviewers mention.  It is thin, but it works flawlessly in my printer and sheets pull individually without getting stuck together.  If you're using this in a copy machine or for work purposes and require a certain weight/thickness or color, then maybe this isn't for you.  However, I never would have noticed a single issue if I hadn't read the reviews beforehand.  For the price, it was worth taking a chance.  I'm glad I did because the paper quality and price surpasses what I can buy locally.

In the 25 page report I just printed, there were 7 pages that didn't feed correctly and parts of those printed on 2 sheets or missed lines on the top or bottom, plus 7 extra pages fed with no printing on them.  I had to check every page to see which ones to reprint.  The printer's fine and I’d fanned the edges before I loaded it.  I've never had this problem with any other paper.Also the paper wrapping around each ream is very thin and arrived torn all over.  I had to handle them carefully to make sure they didn’t tear open completely and leave me with unwrapped reams.  ...not a big deal compared to the paper quality itself, but still annoying and they looked messy when they were stacked on the shelf.  Wish I’d taken a photo before I packed them up to return.

This is the second time I've purchased AmazonBasics copy paper for my home inkjet printer.  I had been purchasing from Staples, but find I am liking buying this item from Amazon far better.  The paper is very good quality and feeds well through the printer - - and most of my printing is two sided!  I am actually experiencing fewer paper jams than with other brands.  A big plus for me is that with Amazon, I can get a really good price without buying a HUGH quantity.  Now, I just buy three reams at a time and it's shipped straight to my door.  I've also used it with some art projects involving photo transfer and have been please with the results.

It was frustrating to see that the paper was damaged upon opening the shipping box.  The outside shipping box was in perfect condition.  However, because the shipping box was bigger than the box of 8 reams of paper - it shifted in the shipping process causing 3 reams to break open.  2 of the reams are damaged beyond use.  Very frustrating that something as simple as packing this properly has now caused wasted work-time.

I ordered Amazon Basics paper before, it was made in France. It was great paper with smooth finish. Loved it so I ordered more recently. When I received the order, I noticed that the paper was made in USA. The smooth finish was gone with the name of "France". Now, the AmazonBasics paper just a regular paper, no different with other brands. I may order more in the further, but I won't be excited when I receive it.

I last had a printer about 10 years ago, until just recently, when I succumbed to the need and bought myself an HP Inkjet. I don't really print much, but when I need to, it's a real pain. I didn't want to spend a lot on paper, and luckily I found this. As usual, Amazon Basic brand turns out to be excellent. The paper is great quality, thick, very white, and prints very well on an HP Inkjet. This pack has three reams of 500 pages each, for $5/ream, which is an excellent price for paper of this quality. It's going to take me about 4 years to go through this much paper, but when I finally finish it off, I'll happily buy another case. Good purchase.

I bought a case of this paper on October 5, 2018.  It seems like very nice paper and of good quality.  But it does not play nice with my fairly new HP Officejet Pro 8610 printer.  My printer is sometimes grabbing 2 sheets instead of 1.  So I end up with 1 sheet with maybe the top 1" printed and then the rest of the print is on the second page.  I've uninstalled my printer and reinstalled it plus ensured I had the latest software.  I've also aligned and adjusted it several times.  I also cleaned all the paper pickup rollers with rubbing alcohol, all to no avail.  I had to print an 80 page document yesterday and ruined 35 pages in the process.  My last case of paper lasted me about a year but the way it's going I'll probably go through this case in half the time.  I've also tried fanning the paper out because sometimes static electricity will bind pages together as well as not fanning out the paper with no success either way.Bottom line is I will be buying a different paper the next time.  Again, it's nice paper but it may not necessarily work correctly with your printer.

It can be a little tough to write a review that opposes so many other reviews. It sets us up for criticism. That said - there is no way we can recommend this paper.PROS - The container size (half carton/5 reams) is great. Love it. So much easier to carry and store. The price of $16 or $17 is good. It was shipped quickly and in good condition. These pros also apply for Georgia-Pacific Spectrum Standard 92 Multipurpose Paper and other competitors.

UPDATE: I still had two reams of this from an order and decided I should use it up before breaking up my new case of other paper. The document I was printing had 103 pages. My printer jammed 21 times using this paper while trying to print that document. Downgrading to one star. I ended up just throwing the rest of my Amazon paper stock into the recycling bin. Not worth the frustration.ORIGINAL REVIEW:

ITS PRINTER PAPER! Has not spontaneously combusted or exploded. Does not smell bad. Lays flat when left alone. Ink seems to stick well to surface. Cuts with scissors. Will catch fire if a match is held to it, so that’s worth noting. Would not recommend for boat building or making farming implements but it’s a fine printer paper.

If you work in an office and know your paper, YOU WILL NOT LIKE THIS PAPER!  I decided to try it out and it is super slick so not all of our printers are able to pull it efficiently.  The bigger problem I have, is that for some reason it curls when it gets heated, like when it goes through a laser printer.  It might work OK with an ink jet printer where no heat is used, but if you're using a laser printer, I'd advise against buying this paper. I honestly don't know what causes that, but its a problem.  Another thing to note is that if you don't like plastic, the ream wrappers seem to be plastic coasted paper, so it can't go into a paper recycling bin.  It's worth it to pay more for a better quality paper.

After reading reviews indicating that the paper was thin and poor quality, I was hesitant to purchase this product but decided to do so because it was the lowest price ream of paper offered.  I am glad to say that I had no reason to be concerned.  The paper is good quality.  It is not thick but it is not very thin either.  The sheets of paper are consistent in size and perfect for every day use which is what I needed.  I find that all AmazonBasics products that I have purchased have been of high quality at a great point.  This one is no different.  I will be purxhasing again.

Just got the paper and this is how it arrived. The paper is all a part of the back to school supplied, and what the classrooms require us to bring. Not sure how I'm supposed to hand this over like this. Very surprising. Not only are they both open, but the top of one of them looks torn. Quite surprising because it is an Amazon product. Disappointing.

WILL NOT FEEDThe paper will not feed in my Canon inkjet printer. I've tried fanning the paper before loading and loading such that the pages are staggered or aligned. It just fails to feed every 10th page or so. It is extremely annoying to go push the reset button every other print. Printer works great for other papers.
The paper is exactly what I expected. It's comparable to other 20lb/92 bright paper I've bought at the office supply store. I do like that I can buy this in smaller packs.

The product was great, it arrived on time and I didn't notice a difference in quality from a slightly more expensive paper. The reason I removed a star was because the paper casing on the reams of paper themselves weren't glued well. As soon as you pick it out of the box the paper casing on the ream immediately will fall apart. It was quite frustrating when 500 sheets of paper went on the floor unexpectedly because of the glue around the ream coming loose. Just be careful removing each ream and you will be fine.For those who want to know where this was manufactured (the paper) it is from France. Like i said though it is just as good as any other regular paper you get but a lot cheaper.

I have to give this paper a one star rating.  I have to spend so much time going through my printed (or copied) pages, to pull out the many blank pages that go through while copying or printing.  I have never had this problem with other brands of paper.  This paper is thin, slick, curls when used in a copier, and if I print out a 15 page document, for instance, or copy multiple page documents, there will be at least 3-5 blank pages stuck throughout each document.  I have to go through everything page by page to take out the extra paper.  Then if I try to put it back in the printer to use that blank paper, it jams.  Too slick, too thin, and the cheaper price isn't worth the hassle of dealing with this paper.  I do know to and always fan out a stack of paper in both directions to make sure it will go through the printer or copier one sheet at a time, but nothing works to keep this paper feedng one sheet at a time.  I ordered a case of 8 reams; I have gone through three reams, trying to make it work, but the other five reams will be donated, I think, to a kindergarten for kids to drawn on.  It's definitely not something I would recommend anyone buying to use as office printing or coping paper.

the product is a good price for the amount of paper you get, but dont expect quick delivery.  I order this on 8/2/18.  the delivery was 8/13/18.  this was the 1st bad sign on a Prime product. On 8/13/18, the delivery was changed to 8/17/17.  On 8/17/18, the delivery was changed to 8/18/18.  On the morning 8/18/18, is showed "Package out to deliver".  Expect by 8p.  at 9p an email received  that delivery is not 8/19-22/18.  no way to trace my package anymore.  It finally got delivered on 8/19.  plan way ahead.The paper has a subtle blue tint.  the thickness of the paper is thinner than the standard 20# paper I normally get and it has a polished feel, like paper used in a fax machine.  I am now concerned based on other reviews that the paper will not feed well in my printer.  one way to find out.  I hope the finish will not coat the feeder rollers on my printers, it will be very difficult to clean those.

I have gone through reams of paper since school started and I needed a less expensive source. I'm hoping this is it. The paper is really nice. Allows me to print what I need. Same brightness and print quality...and it's made in the USA!

Perfectly good office paper for 99% of routine office jobs. In the event you need specialized paper for brightness or thickness, just buy a small amount of that variety--this product is not meant for you. But still buy it for you office. Seriously. You won't need paper for the next 10 years and the price is unbeatable. The only possible drawback is storage space. The box is roughly 20x12x9. Keep that in mind.

I've never bought paper in this quantity before so i was a little shocked when i first saw the package... man was it heavy.The paper itself is thin, but i haven't had any bleeding or excessive feathering so far. I saw some other reviews saying the paper curls from the heat of printing, but I haven't experienced that myself. Still chugging along with the first pack!!!

I just received my replacement ream because the other package was torn open and pages were missing potentially... I have no idea as it was completely ripped open. With 500 pages I was not counting. I asked to return and they said to keep it and they would replace, which is generous (and why I gave 4 stars, not 3), but the new ream was ripped as well. I am not sure if people are running out of paper at the warehouse and grabbing a few pages to print with or if the outside protector wrap is just too thin. The paper is as described. Just hope next time I order, the ream is in tack.

We ordered this exact product a year and a half ago, and it was surprisingly great quality.  Sturdy, bright white, smooth to the touch like premium printer paper.  We reordered the same product recently and the product has degraded in quality while being sold under the same Amazon Basics label.  It's unusually thin, flimsy, slightly rough to the touch (like notebook paper) and just cheap.  I had a couple sheets of the old paper to compare by feel and I noticed the differences.  Not a good business practice for Amazon to lower the quality of a product once good reviews have cemented its sales.

I would say that this paper is a little thicker than i thought it was going to be.  The paper also feels a little bit less flexible than im used to.  I like to draw and write on these with pencil, so this type of paper didn't work as well with pencils/pens as i've had in the past.  However, if you're just using it for printing, then it's great.

i take my training, nutrition, and health pretty seriously.  i am mindful of what i put into my body and it needs to be clean, healthy, and yummy!  this product hits all those important bullets for me.  i appreciate how easy it is to blend this into a shake - even without a shaker bottle!  i prefer the chocolate to the vanilla, but i think that is a personal preference.  i would recommend this protein powder to anyone that is trying to set positive intentions for being healthy.  in a journey that is not always easy this is a life saver.  thumbs up.  way up!

I am very pleased with this paper quality.  It never got stucked (overlapped)  or slipped from rolling the paper out when printing, like other reviews.  I am lucky.  I have a regular office, no high tech equipment with glossy finishes.  You can use this paper quality for regular print-outs.  Even printing coupon is great.  It all depends on your printer.  If you are looking for shiny thick paper quality, then, no this is not for you.  But if you need basic requirements, then this is for you and me.  I am pleased with the paper product.  Will order again..if the price is cheap.

I've seen many negative reviews about this paper. People have said it jams in the printer and is too thin and chalky. I'm glas I didn't listen to this. I have the most basic printer ever and the paper goes right through it without any issues. I've been using it all semester and haven't had a jam once. It is a little thin but its not like its tracing paper thin and it doesnt rip by accident. As for chalkiness...I didn't notice any. I will be buying again when I need to. It's a great price and will last a while.

This paper checks all the boxes. It's a nice bright white it feels substantial more than others I've bought on here and it works very well through my printer my printer on some of the cheap stuff my printer picks up two sheets at a time and with this I have not had that issue so far so far I would highly recommend this paper to anyone and feel good about that recommendation.
This is certainly a great price for a big ream of basic paper.  This will last me a long time and works well in my Canon printer/copier/scanner/fax machine.

This paper is horrible!  I have a home office and utilize multiple laser printers and this paper gets jammed in every single printer.  I am not sure if it is because of the thinness of the paper or the unusual texture.  I will not buy it again.  This box is heading to the recycle bin.

After using 2 reams now does not work on my Epson XP-310. With a chute of 25 pages and it says paper out! Called Epson Tech Services who walked me through all the set up functions and it said the same! They told me something was wrong internally and offered for me to send it to their authorizes service center at my cost! Something didn't feel right so I purchased a pack of HP paper, loaded it and it started printing like it had been doing before the Amazon paper!I must add, here in Central Texas, the weather has been very strange, fog, mist, drizzles and high humidity which may be the reason, so, I would not recommend its use except in dry weather, but even then it might be a waste of money!
I prefer very bright white BUT no one hardly reads materials included with products.Good for non advertising copy.

This is not the link I opened. I remembered clearly that the order I made was for 8 reams paper and $25.59. I even bragged it to my husband that I got a really good deal on it. How could it turned out to be an 5 ream shipping? You can tell me that I didn't pay attention when placed my order, but the link I opened said 8 reams. So disappointed......

It's white and it's paper but I wouldn't buy it again; I pity whoever I decide to give the rest of it to. Meh. The paper is on the thin side so ink shows through making duplex printing a really bad idea unless you want to have a new "solve this report" word game during your next meeting. Grr. Coloring on it with markers is a bad idea since the paper is on the slippery side so the marker smears and also bleeds through the paper. How am I supposed to draw a Picasso during the next 4 hour financial department snooze fest meeting? Argh. Schlepping myself out into the world to get a case of my normal brand, thicker, non-slickery paper. Guess I'll have to interact with real humans. Gasp!

I purchased 3 reams of this paper and I am using it on my trusty HP laser printer, which I have used for years with multipurpose papers purchased from Staples and Target with NO jams/problems.  Using the AmazonBasics 92 Bright Multipurpose Copy Paper in the paper tray ALWAYS jams my printer on pages 2-3 on a multi-page print.  Referring to the Q&A section and product reviews, some customers suggested fanning the stack of paper.  I tried that, and the paper still jammed in the printer.The only way I can avoid paper jams with this AmazonBasics paper on a multi-page print job is to feed the paper manually one-by-one into the laser printer - totally NOT convenient.  Technically the print quality of the paper for single-sided prints is fine, but either the thinness or the slickness of the paper is causing the paper to jam in my laser printer.

When the paper runs through and doesn't jam, the print quality is good. Problem is it frequently jams up the printer and I have to open the back cover, take out the toner cartridge, manually pull out the jammed paper. What a huge pain in the rear. Other paper stock I've purchased from the usual big box office stores- I do not have this problem. Paper is good for the grandkids to draw on but not dependable for the printer. I will not buy again.

Would not order AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper again. Keeps jamming !  None of the other paper, including the Rely Brand, order at the same time keeps causing paper jams like the AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper.  Have no idea why but tried less paper, fanning and separating the sheet, nothing worked!

This paper is fine. Some of the pages at the edge were a little rippled but didn't affect printing in my laser printer. The reams were sealed in moist proof paper. Good for making copies of receipts when you need payment confirmation or whatever. Good to draw on as well. Nothing fancy just good paper enough to document with save & store until you shred it years down the road. Paper bright and clean. The box mine came in was reusable, cute & sturdy! :)

I'm not sure I can convey how life-changing this copy paper is. Don't let the "AmazonBasics" fool you, because this paper is NOT "basic." It is transformative. It is paper-thin. It is rectangular. It is so white, it is practically the Oscars. It is manufactured to the highest standards: the short side is 8.5 inches -- no more, no less -- while the long side is a precise 11 inches. In the past, I have used paper from Xerox, or Staples, or Office Depot. Never again! Those papers do not have the power, the impact, the modest simplicity yet endless potential, of AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper.

Got the paper, needed it in a hurry, and wasn't able to go out, so amazon was my last resort.  Had to throw the paper out.  It was slick and difficult to feed, but worse than that was a sickeningly sweet chemical smell coming off the whole ream of paper.Went to Walmart and got a ream of paper for half the cost of this.  Disappointed, most of the amazonbasics items have been top notch.

Update: Now, having tried to use five more reams since my original review, I have measured an average jam rate of 4% (4 sheets per hundred pages or 20 sheets per ream). As other reviewers note, the paper tends to curl when in the printer. It is almost impossible to use for two-sided printing.Original review: I have purchased this product several times and have noticed what appears to be a decline in its quality. I have measured a jam rate as high as almost 6% in the most recent ream that I used (28 sheets per 500) and the typical jam rate is between 1% and 2%. Other papers of the same advertised weight or heavier perform flawlessly in the same printer, at a zero jam rate over thousands of pages.

I've used several different types of paper, and never had any trouble until I used the Amazon basics paper. This paper frequently misfeeds, fails to feed, or jams in my printer that has not had any issue with any other paper that I've fed it. Most Amazon basics products are great and a great value, but the savings on this paper isn't worth the hassle. Wish I'd just bought a little instead of a case of it.
The last thing you want to worry about in a business is paper curling up in the printer and making a mess.Do not buy this paper. It is horrible.
2 reams were damaged upon arrival. as well as the box. Some paper was wrinkled and not able to go thru the printer.after completely  unpacking all the paper in the box, every package is ripped open.

This isn't the best paper you'll ever encounter in your life, but for about $3-4/ream, it's pretty decent. If you're looking for massive quantities of relatively cheap paper, this is what you need. I use about a ream of this stuff a day and it's perfectly fine.Pros:

This paper is pretty awful.  We have been using Hammermill which is 20-pound weight and 92 brightness, just like this is advertised so I assumed it would be 20-lb.  It is a little thicker than tissue paper but not much.  It wrinkles and tears easily.  Every 3rd or 4th copy comes out flat and untorn.  It is a total disaster in the copier.  We use a ream a day so it isn't sitting in the copier "getting damp."  Spend $3 more and get Hammermill.  I am very disappointed.
Worst paper for jams. Had to remove jams about every 10th sheet. Went to Staples and bought their cheapest which is working much better. Gave this stuff to my granddaughter for coloring.

This is ultimately my own fault, I know.  But I also think this represents some slimy marketing practices on Amazon's part.  When you go to the copy paper section, you have the option to filter by size.  And when I chose 8.5x14 - legal sized paper... this is the top option that came up.  And the Amazon letter-size paper is featured more than once on the first page of results.  I was in a hurry and made the mistake of trusting that Amazon's filters would work as designed on their own product, so now I've wasted money on the wrong size paper.  Scummy work, Amazon - you make plenty of money without engaging in mildly deceptive practices to make more sales.

I started a home-based business about a year ago and was looking for an affordable nd convenient option for my paper needs because I work a lot with contracts.This paper has worked great in my printer from day one. We haven't noticed a single blemish or issue with any sheet, and it shows colors and everything else very well. The paper has never jammed or made of my printing jobs look low quality.

This is a pretty straightforward purchase. It prints just fine both color and black ink. Arrived safely - though, fun story, it was raining cats and dogs the day this was delivered so if I wasn't home when it arrived, it would have been damaged by the rain because there wasn't any additional packaging in the box (which is fine, less waste). So advice: if you don't have a spot on your porch that can protect it from rain, and it's supposed to rain that day, just wait to order (or be home).

The paper has a slippery quality that does not feed well through a laser printer, and nearly destroyed mine on multiple occasions with the jamming it caused. I was excited to buy a five-ream quantity (a discount, but not too much to keep on hand), but paper attempting to ruin my printer is a serious downside.

We have ordered this paper several times now for multiple business and personal uses.  The heavy box always arrives in good shape. The paper itself is a good value for the price.  I have no complaints on the quality at all.  It is the same as many name brand papers we have tried.  The brightness is also perfect.

The box the paper is in arrived in horrible, beat up shape even inside another box.  The packaging of each ream was bent, torn, not glued together, and just a mess.  The paper seems to be fine, but the packaging is terrible and makes me feel like this paper isn't worth it.

It's printer paper and it was a decent price.  Doesn't jam my ancient laser printer.Not much else to say about printer paper.  Why am I reviewing printer paper you ask?  Covid19 lockdown that's why.  Weather stinks, can't go outside, might as well review all the stuff I buy on Amazon right?

The paper was delivered already opened and half way out of its packaging. All of the paper was not damaged, however some was. And I cannot put it back in its packaging, so now I have 500 sheets (minus the damaged paper) just loosely around.I'm only giving it 1 star because of how it arrived. Other than that issue, it seems to be amazing quality and brightness.

I really don't get why everyone's complaining.  This isn't high-quality paper, that's for sure, but it works fine for normal everyday use.  I personally have a Brother MFC-J995DW Inkvestment printer and have had absolutely no issues whatsoever with this paper.  My wife prints a lot for her job as a pre-school teacher and also for her scrapbooking hobby and this works perfectly for her.  She has also said that it laminates well with her AmazonBasics laminater and cuts well on her Cricut® Explore Air 2.  So really we have no complaints at all.

When I saw Amazon selling 3 case ream  (1,500 sheets!!) of this at $9.82 I didn't even think twice and hit the purchase now button. Item was unavailable at the said time, so I'm guessing that might account for the price drop. But who's complaining, right? There was no way I was going to pass on this especially since we use this a lot in the house.Personally, I do not believe you can get a better price anywhere, especially if you consider that this is the average going brand price for a single ream of 500 sheets.. The paper quality is at par with brand names so I have next to no complaints in that area.

YOu have customer service link that does not provide service.  I try to chat--you give me options that you wrote but leave no room for me to tell you what the problem really is.  I once had a direct call #, but lost that phone--my bad.I am a regular Kindle Book buyer, and you used to tell me if I already have that book If I should reorder or if I have preorderred, you telll me I did that already.  Not today--I duplicated a pre-order.  I have paid twice for the same book before and it is near impossible to get a refund.  My" kindle book orders" shows 4 books, and I have easily bought over 300.  Wake up people--we have been prime members for several years, and people are putting out comments that we should not trust you--wjhy is that--I just want a intelligent way to contact someone in you world.

I go through a lot of printer paper on a weekly basis. Most of this is for documents that are saved as in office files or for rough drafts of documents. Going to the store for individual boxes of paper has been a pet peeve for awhile.This paper came right to my door with free shipping with prime. The paper itself is packaged well and none of the individual packages were damaged. The paper loads and prints well. The paper seems a little thin but this is actually a benefit for the type of work that I do. I would think twice about using this for finished projects for clients but this is an all around great all purpose office paper.

I was very disappointed with this purchase. Normally I buy name brand printer paper, but I figured that Amazon Basics paper would likely be similar to other brands, it’s just paper after all. I bought two cases of it, now I just have two cases of scratch paper because this stuff jams up my laser printer almost every other page I print. I have never had a jam before I bought this paper. I would highly recommend people stay away from this product. Now that I bought new paper by HP I haven’t had a single jam.

I bought this paper for use in my HP LaserJet and it works great. The paper is heavy (compared to the cheap crapole most office use) and print quality was good. I'm knocking one star off my rating as this paper says it is 92 brightness but to me looks a bit like really nice newspaper. Don't get me wrong it doesn't look bad or yellow, it just looks dingier than I expected, I like my paper to be a bright crisp white.I would definitely buy this paper again provide I can't find something with a higher white level at the same price.

I purchased this just recently based on a satisfied purchase in October 2018. But the paper has changed.Pros: It's still a 92 brightness. It prints very nicely no jamming nor multi page feeds. The (10/18) paper seemed to have static electricity, and would stick to itself making it difficult to straighten a printed stack. This doesn't have that static. The paper does seem to accept the toner well, so prints look crisp and brilliant.

Bought this for office use in faxes and a laser printer. The finish on this paper is a little odd in that it has a very slight blue cast to it (which for us is no big deal) and it is very smooth. The smooth part is a problem for our laser printer as it has a hard time feeding it through the machine so we are having to un-jam the machine a lot. This didn't happen with other paper we have that has a little rougher texture. We don't have that problem with our fax machines. The price is very good for the paper and we put more paper through the faxes then the printer, so we may just end up getting a few reams if the previous paper for the laser printer. Ya I know that is a little weird.
Very thin compared with other papers of same weight. Can't print on both sides and read either side because it bleeds through! Very disappointed with the quality.

We have a home based business and use a lot of paper, so I thought I'd try to save us some money and purchase the Amazon Basics Multipurpose Copy Paper.  I should have listened to my gut because going cheaper doesn't always equal same quality.  The paper prints nicely but that's about it.  When I file papers, this copy paper folds and bends very easily instead of laying flat like I'd hope it would.  We scan all of our paperwork to avoid having piles of papers in our office on a daily basis.  While the image of the scanned paper turns out nice, to get there means having to unjam my printer on just about every scan.  The paper gets stuck and often tears mid-scan.  As a result, I will be returning to our local office supply store and purchasing their brand of copy paper which has always worked nice.  It is worth spendng a few extra dollars so we don't have the headache of the thin Amazon paper.

Consistently jams my HP LaserJet 4000 printer.  This printer is almost 20 years old and has successfully used many, many different brands of paper in it's long career.  As soon as I started using the the AmazonBasics paper, the printer started jamming.  Now it jams almost every time I print.  As soon as I switch back to another brand of paper, it stops jamming.

Hey, I acknowledge my Brother MFC8840D is an old laser printer.  Maybe it's lost a feeding step, but I never had regular paper jams before I started using this paper.  Seems to feed okay up top, but the paper keeps clipping the insertion feed from the main tray (even after all the cleaning/fanning steps).  Switched to 24 lb paper of  another brand, and the jams totally went away.  Paper seems fine to the touch, and I'm no paper guru, so I can't say what's not optimal about it.  Amazon's features listing should include a stars rating for "works in my printer".
Brought a 5 ream package.The shipping package was fine. No problem.

I am not sure if the paper got wet/damp in the warehouse or in shipping but every time I make a copy the paper comes out curled.  See picture.  And I mean EVERY copy in the whole ream comes out this way and ends up falling out of the copy machine because they are so curled.

This paper is effective for our office use. It meets our minimum weight for our laser jet printer and holds up well when there are several hundred prints rolling off the line. I have no issues with colors popping on this paper, and no issues with bleeding or smearing. Again, I do have a laser machine so that may have an impact on our prints. The paper is just as good, if not better, than a brand priced three times as much. The weight is good and it POPS if you make a standard paper pop toy and test it out. Some find that a good test of paper and durability. It's a true white paper and no issues with this. I will definitely purchase more reams.

The paper is too thin, curls when heated and subsequently can not be scanned anymore. It may work for throw away stuff, but is not professional or useable for documents. It is also too rough to use as toilet paper. In addition, the packaging is awful and the reams will arrive damaged which happened in the two times I ordered it. While convenient to get it delivered, the quality is really unacceptable. And yes the packaging can not be recycled. What a waist of money and time.

Paper is thinner than we realized. It works with our Laserjet printer, but we may not get this brand of paper next time. If you need to print letter or formal documentation, consider a thicker paper and skip this one. If you just need to print for yourself at home, this gets the job done.You may be disappointed with this grade of paper if you need to print photos on an inkjet.

I've never experienced constant paper jamming in my printers prior.  I've typically bought a case of paper from Staples or Office Depot 2-4 times per year so I print a lot.  This paper comes out with 2-8 sheets at a time and sometimes a page will print over 2 pages.  I fan it, reassort it and put it back in but doesn't seem to help.  It may be less expensive but the amount of time I  have to waste managing it is not worth the cost savings.  Of course you cannot determine this until you have used it for a while - that it is the paper and not the printer.  Too bad for me.  There will be a new reason it cannot be returned.
It's cheaper than most, a bright white too.A little on the thin side, hasn't given me any trouble going through laser printer, just curls up on sides from the heat of printer.

I order this paper for our small office (less than 20 employees) and we have it set for subscription. We’re nearly entirely paperless but do need to make copies of certain documents and such, and this paper is perfect for just that! It’s not thick and it’s not the brightest - but if you’re not needing fancy schmancy paper for presentation, then this will do just fine for you! Early on, we did have a couple reams that arrived damaged on one single delivery and Amazon was quick to correct the issue...so don’t let that or all of the other reviews that claim this deter you; this is great paper for the price and the best part is that you don’t have to go to the store and lug it back to your office!

While the color and finish of this paper are very good and the price is a real bargain, it is so thin that it does not lay flat after printing in my color laser multifunction machine .  As a result copies and printed pages are hard to handle and documents meant to be shared are not fit for presentation.  Even more frustrating is that the curled pages jam up the auto-feeder when I try to make copies.

Maybe I am just easy to please, or maybe I got lucky, but this paper is great. For what we paid vs what we got I am very happy. I kind of like the "downside" of the top rated bad comment.. which is that this paper is thin. I hate double sided prints and with how much storing of files we do I can appreciate this lighter weight stuff. Small businesses, home, college.. this is the perfect paper. If you're churning out collated binders and stuff I'd definitely go with a heavyweight. I am Very pleased with it. Kinda neat having Amazon branded reems laying around either.Only issue I had was the free shipping. I don't have prime which is probably my own dumb fault. But! The next option after free was 20 dollars which was rediculous cause at that point I'm paying more then the name brand shipped. The free shipping was bad.. Took a week and a half. I was stealing teems from 10 year old printers upstairs while I waited and barely made it. I'd say all around I'd have been nothing but happy if the shipping had been more reasonable.

We bought this Officeworld/Compatible with Canon Maxify 1200 ink in, Feb 2018. The Original Officeworld box says Production Date 2/27/2018 and Expiration 2/27/2020.  It is October 2018- The XL black is still half full, and the other 3 colors are full.  Even so,  we are having blank pages, blurry pages, etc... We have Cleaned, Deep Cleaned, and Aligned the printer head many times in the past 2 weeks.. Sometimes,  we get a great page.. Other times it is blank or blurry. We did the “ Manual Removal” of the Officeworld/Compatible with Canon Maxify 1200 XL Black ( Against Canon Customer Service advice), put in a second  Officeworld/Compatible with Canon Maxify 1200 XL Black and still we’re having the same troubles... Stick with Canon ink for Canon printers. This has been a real headache...

Can you review paper? I mean it isn't like wine...there is no aroma of wood or fruit...we can't swish it around in a glass and talk in British accents while nodding in review over a marble table.We CAN crumple it, draw on it, use inks on it, fold it, shove it in our overworked printers and pray it doesn't cause a jam.

This is the  first time I bought this brand of copy paper and I'm glad I did. It is every bit as good as the more expensive paper and costs less. It's just thick enough and sturdy; doesn't tear easy and no ink of any kind smears. My grandchildren love it for coloring and it holds up, even through toddler scribbling. You can't beat it for the price.

I needed a ton of paper cheap because our toddler loves coloring and whenever I do need to print something, it’s never for a presentation or anything professional. But, like other complaints, the papers stick so sometimes my one page print comes out across two pieces of paper. Next time I’ll probably opt for cheap coloring paper and a pack of good printer paper.

We bought this paper just to save ourselves a trip to the office supply store, but it turns out not only to be OK, it's the best printer/copier paper we've found.  It doesn't curl up after printing in our older LaserJet, and also works fine in our recent inkjet all-in-one.  When we run out, we'll order this again for sure.

It's a great deal - $25 for 2500 pages. Printer paper isn't super thick or super thin, just pretty average, which is what I would expect for the price. However, it curls up in laser printers...fairly maddening. I'm not sure if it does it on inkjet printers, and I assume it does on laser printers because of the heat generated during printing. But if you want OK quality and a large quantity? This is the item for you, so long as somewhat curled pages don't bother you a lot.

We've been having trouble with the paper at work that the office supply company provides us since they switched to a recycled brand.  A friend gave us a ream of this paper to try.  It was great so we ordered a case.  The results are great, very few jams (I'm thinking this is more the old printer's fault) and we'll be placing another order soon.  The weight is good and you can do double sided just fine.

I picked up a 1000 sheets, the first 50 resulted in 25 double feeds on a Brother Inkjet. Given the time and ink wasted, not going to even try the remaining 950. Back to the Hammermill multi-purpose 99.99 Jam Free.

My company has a Konica Minolta C658 Laser printer which has worked great for thousands of copies.  But the 1st two sheets of this paper caused jams, and the next several sheets, while not jamming, missfed as demonstrated by the crooked printed images.  However the first two pages through my home HP LaserJet P2055dn fed without problems so I will be using this paper at home, not at work, and will not be reordering.

AmazonBasics 92 copy paper is excellent. The 500 sheets per pack at this price is a definite plus. The paper was enclosed in a vinyl sleeve at manufacturing and Team Amazon shipped it in a cardboard box so it arrived in a pristine condition. I continue to be pleased with the AmazonBasics line.

This is a decent thick paper for the price! I was very pleased to see that it is opaque and of a nice smooth quality. It does have a cool cast to it; but under full light is as bright as some top quality expensive brands. Definitely has become my office go-to based on price and quality.

The price for this paper was an unbelievably good deal.  I am still using it and it has never jammed my Epson Inkjet printer or put out a bad copy. I like the size of three reams and a sturdy box with removable lid. A bigger size would be too hard for me to handle as I'm 70 with back and leg issues.  This size is perfect.

If you're like my house, the printer works full time. We always need ink or paper. I came across thia great deal by Amazon and decided to try it out, boy am I glad. No reason to pay more for another brand. Amazon knocks it out of the park. Quality paper, prints well, and comes in a well constructed cardboard storage. Will definitely order again!

Judging by other reviews, I must be lucky. I've ordered two of the 3 ream size and they have both arrived intact and perfectly fine. Yes, it's cheap paper, but seems to work just fine in my cheap Brother laser printer/copier. No problems, acceptable brightness, and it just works. Very good price for delivered paper.

Well, I've run a few cases of this stuff trough my Xerox 700 and V80 and it's about what you'd expect. Cheep 20 lb. bond. It's probably about the cheapest quality paper you can buy right now. It feels a bit flimsier than the Hammermill and when the prices are similar I always go with the Hammermill...
Came open and some papers damaged. The box was fully closed. The  box was fully closed. So it seems thats how it was packed. Disappointed. Should’ve gotten the HP brand
The paper is too thin and jams in my wonderful Brother printer.If Amazon wishes to have different paper prices, have various grades of paper available.

The product was delivered today two weeks late than the original order. Additionally, the package was destroyed. The product could be good, but it turned out bad for the low quality of the shipping service. Supper disappointed as we needed to go to staples to get the similar product.

Based on some other reviews it looks like this paper has quite a bit of variability between batches.The paper we received has slightly rough edges, so the paper sticks together, causing the printer to feed multiple sheets at once and jam.  Every few pages the printer feeds 5-20 sheets at once. I bet this isn't great for the printer.

My box arrived and when I opened it I found a ream of paper that had been ripped open all ready so I'm not even sure if all of the product is there or not. Very disappointed considering the price for the paper. Will not be ordering again. Next time I'll just go to walmart.

This paper is OK, it's a little thin so consider that if you do a lot of double-sided printing. We use this paper for casual home office use and school work, so the quality is fine for us. In a professional setting or for schoolwork that is significant, I probably would spring for a whiter, thicker paper.

The copy paper works fine.  My only issue is that, when the package arrives, both reams of paper I had ordered were unsealed.  All the paper was there but the glue that was supposed to hold the reams intact didn't do so.  The shipping box was small enough to prevent the paper from sliding around.  It wasn't worth it to me to return the paper.  My concern, however, is that opened copy paper might absorb some measure of moisture before I can use it all.

I love the fact that I could get a box of just 5 reams of paper.  One ream is not enough, and an entire carton is too much for my needs.  Paper works well, no jams. Paper works in both my printer, and my copy machine.  Price is very reasonable. As an unexpected bonus, the smaller heavy cardboard box the paper came in, is a nice little box to be able to reuse for packing, shipping something yourself, etc.

I won’t lie, this Amazon paper is pretty good.  It’s so much easier to have the paper delivered than personally going and buying it and having to lift it.  It’s great paper and thee price point is fantastic.  I will definitely be getting this paper again  and having it delivered to the office.  Don’t work harder, work smarter.

I got it for overnight shipping, so it definitely saved my day. The paper is great.So far I had no paper jamming issue. Also its weight is just perfect not too heavy even if I make 500 pages of folder and not too light - you cannot see through the paper. Definitely recommend it to someone who prints folder after folder.
The paper works well in my printer, scanner, copier.It is the right brightness for my purposes. I am a college professor who creates documents and copies of tests etc for students.

I needed these for home use for simple text based documents and they’re good for that. The paper seems a bit thin - sometimes the printer grabs a couple when it means to grab one - but it’s not an issue (I just end up with an extra blank page in the output tray). If you just need something basic and cheap, these are it.

All reams came opened due to horrendous packaging.Only reason I'm not returning because it will be a hassle and most of the paper is usable for my home needs. And the price is much lower than others. I will look into buying local next time.

As a business owner I’m always looking for a ways to cut down on the spending and printer paper is a must have I use plenty of it and this is a great but the price is decent and you get plenty of paper

It feeds through my Brother Laser printer just fine. I can see what's printed on it just fine. If that's all you need--great. However, if like me, you need to be able to tape the pages together, like for multipage patterns or diagrams, this won't do. Scotch tape and painters tape just release after about a day.

Price-wise, this paper is hard to beat. It's nearly perfect as an everyday paper ... and did I say the price was hard to beat?True be told, I prefer a higher weight paper. However, I actually chose to order this paper -- rather than the more expensive, higher pound brand-name paper which I had been ordering -- because I have been printing things to be stapled and things which are everyday ... for those purposes, this paper is just right.

I've purchase several of "Amazon's Basic" brands and found that their products are top-notch and equal or better than the leading competitors product with a much lower cost.  This copy paper is good quality, great value, runs through the printer easy and you don't have to leave the house to lug home a box of heavy paper from the office supply store...A No-Brainer!

Disappointment in Amazon and myself. Distracted by kids I didn't really pay attention to the fact that I was buying 1 ream at $10.  When it arrived and I saw that, I was annoyed, when I opened it and the wrapping was all ripped I was even more irritated. And when I checked what I'd ordered and saw it was 10 dollars... Ugh. Amazon basics are usually well priced for good quality. This is a fail.

I'm a big fan of paper made in France so I took a chance with a team of the Amazon Basics copy paper. The cost team was sort of banged up when it arrived but the replacement ream was in good shape. It is indeed white paper, paper thin sheets (pun intended) which are smooth to the touch. This is why I love paper made in France. Printing is fine, writing on it is fine, cutting or tearing it is fine, and it can be folded into soaring airplane forms.

If you don't want to buy a box of ten reams of paper, but you are tired of buying one ream at a time (often at a cost of $7-$8 per ream); then this carton of three reams is perfect.  The paper is of good quality and the box is well made, so it won't fall apart on you, before you can get to the third and last ream.  The price is nice too; seriously, $15 for three reams of paper is a very good deal.  If you have Prime, then it is even better, since you'll have it at your door in a day or two, without having to lug home a box of paper.  Thank you, thank you Amazon!

I can't believe I'm having to write a negative review about printing paper!  But this paper is the absolute worse I've ever come upon. My toilet paper is thicker than this paper - just had an idea of what I might be able to use this for.  I blame myself for trying to save a few bucks - never again.

I work from home so I have to pay for all of my own office supplies.  My biggest annual expense is printer paper so I am always trying to find the best deals here on Amazon.  Most commodity grade 20lb bond is going for roughly $5/ream right now so when I found this deal at a little over $3/ream I ordered immediately.  The paper arrived two days earlier than expected which was just an added bonus.

Buying paper in bulk really saves money. It may take me ten years to use all of this paper, given that I don't print all that much, but it is certainly quality paper and the price was fantastic. Works great with my HP Ink Jet printer, although I haven't tried it with any laser printers. I'm sure it would work just as well though.

As a student on a budget who is required to print ungodly amounts of class materials on a weekly basis, this paper has completely met my needs. You can't beat the value.  Some folks have complained that this paper is too thin, and while I wouldn't use it for a resume or professional letter, it's been perfectly adequate for me. I've even recycled my pages from the previous semester and have reprinted on the backside (so obviously the paper is not THAT thin). By recycling my paper, this package has lasted me over a year.I use a basic HP Envy scan/copy/printer.

I used to buy my printer paper at Target or Walmart when it was on sale, but this price and quantity is perfect for me. It should last a long time. My husband was surprised when this large box arrived, but I found a place in the office closet to store it, so he's happy now. (Storage space is an issue for us). Happy with this purchase.
This computer paper is so cheap the printer cant even catch it to draw it into the print. Absolute garbage, I wouldn't buy this. Save yourself a lot of frustration!

More reasonable than other paper brands for the quantity. 1st 4 sheets seemed they did not print well, but after that it's been fine.Not much to say about paper if it prints. Not high quality resume paper or for other documents, but for daily laser printing its a good deal.

I want to be fair:  I bount this in July 2017, as part of a one-ream offer, for under $4.00; it does not appear to be offered anymore in a single ream.  Therefore, it's possible that Amazon is now using a different manufacturer/supplier.However, this paper jams my Canon MG6800 printer or fails to feed.  I have flipped the paper more times than a pancake, hoping that whatever is causing the problem (something in the manufactuering, a coating, storage?) is moved away from the feeding mechanism or the rollers. Unlike other buyers, I did not notice a blue or yellow hue.

If you like paper jams, this is the paper for you. I have never had a problem with paper jams in my Brother MFC-9560 CDW until I used this paper. The only way to avoid jamming with this paper was to only fill the cassette halfway and to thoroughly fan the paper before putting it in. Spend the extra dollar and buy a better paper.

It's nice paper. What can I say? I just print out work emails and the occasional online coupon so I'm not exactly doing any high quality printing here. It works for my needs and I don't notice any issues. I would not use this for high quality photos/pictures but that's pretty obvious.

Every single paper order I've placed and received through Amazon has had very disappointing delivery quality where there is consistent damage to the paper's packaging. To be fair, none of the deliveries have damaged the paper itself - just the packaging, which is only frustrating for transport/storage purposes.I've discovered that the packaging damage is less severe when ordering individual reams as opposed to any case, but this gets pricey when you have to order several individual reams.

I homeschool, and my daughter is crafty, which means we go through a LOT of paper. I use this in my laser printer for work and for homeschooling. Buying in bulk like this (we bought eight reams) saves us money and it makes sure we have enough for the next six months or so.

Awesome that Amazon has its own Basic necessity products.  The quality of the paper is great and I not thin at all for the price. It stand up to other brands that are sold at stores for the same or higher price in the same paper weight range. The perk is that I get it delivered to my home with out having to carry it from the store. Great buy and my go to purchase when I am out of printing paper.

I am sure there is better paper out there - but I didnt need high quality paper.  I just needed paper.  And this price was great and getting it via Prime is awesome.  I dont know a lot about paper - but I have seen plenty of it like most people.  so when I got this, I did not have any part of me say "this is not good paper".  It was just paper, simple and exactly what I needed.  I would order this again and again.

The paper was okay at first but one day it started printing on a long, continuous line (even longer than a CVS/Longs receipt)!  That section of the paper was barely perforated - not cut at all.  This will be my last time buying this product.

My regular paper. My reorder was not available ordered this paper description seemed the same but who knows.  I will be careful NOT to accidentally reorder this paper in the future.  I don't like to re-shop items when it is time for a reorder. that's a task for another time . Hope this helps.

I purchased this paper thinking I was getting a good deal - I mean... Paper is paper, right?Unfortunately the savings are not worth the deal! This paper is thin and kind of slippery, for lack of a better word. I use a Brother Laserjet printer, and the pages come out curled around the edges. If I'm printing a large quantity at once, I have to stop in between and pull smaller stacks off the tray or the curled pages will push pages out of or off, the stack onto the floor, causing a mess. But also, totally messing up the stack so that I have to go back and re-order the documents.

I was very low on printer paper and wasn't sure when I'd be getting to a store for more. I was going to order a different brand but for what I'm using it for (mainly coupons) I figured I'd try Amazon's brand since it was a few dollar cheaper for the same amount of paper. I'm glad I did. It's perfect for what I'm using it for. Would definitely order it again if I need it. It's great to have the option when I can't get to a store.

Purchased two boxes.  Unfortunately, the boxes didn't mate and procreate.  So I have to purchase more boxes from Amazon to meet my needs.  Probably received two males boxes or two female boxes.  I'll be looking for mates in my next order.  Then again, they may have used contraception.

I hate buying things like copy paper from a retail store.  It is heavy and bulky.  Buying online is so much nicer.We used a lot of this to print off school work.  It is fine.  If you need a higher quality paper, you should invest in it - this is more general use.  Good enough for 99% of my use cases.

I generally find buying printer paper to be a big pain in the butt...especially lugging it from store to car to house.  This paper is really good, and at a good price, plus it is delivered to my door !!!  One less thing to bog down your day...it took buying paper from a dreaded task to not a big deal.

This is usable paper. No problem that I can think of. There was a couple of paper jams that I know of over the last several weeks. I don't think that is much worse than any other copy paper that I have used and I really can't blame the paper for the paper jams. I don't really know what the cause of that was.I will continue to get copy paper from Amazon since I had bad dealing with the local Staples with their crazy (waste my time) reward system. They can go out of business for all I care. If you get your toner elsewhere, other than Amazon, then I suggest you check the prices at Amazon, because the cost at Staples isn't even close to Amazon.

I am no paper pro, so I can’t speak about the quality of the paper itself - works great for my home use. I am qualified to find it unfortunate that the glue used to close the ream package ends also glued a chunk of papers together, in two out of two teams so far.

We've been using this paper at work for months. Sometimes it seems a little thin... but still not having any issues or complaints. This is definitely my go-to paper source.Pro-tip - the 8 ream case is much cheaper than the 10 ream case. Get 2 of them for nearly the price of one. :)

How much can you say about basic copy paper? This paper is just as good as anything I can get from any local office supply, or big-box store. It just costs less money and is a very good value. Plus, I don't have to leave home and spend my time to get it. It just shows up at my front door in a day or two!
When I opened the box to the paper cover was completely ripped off. Can't even Carrier it without the paper falling out.

I am happy with print quality. I bought this thinking I would be getting a better deal due to it being an "Amazon Basics" product. Sadly, no sooner did this arrive, did I find I had paiD' more than  I would have paid for Staples or Office Depot paper. Lesson learned!

Though this paper is just a little lighter weight than I usually buy, I purchased it because I needed more than usual, and the price for the half-case of reams was great. I've been totally satisfied with the paper, and probably will never buy any other type of (regular) printer paper again.

Yo be honest this Printing papers are way expensive...you get 5,000 printing paper for $24.99 at Walmart...Can’t beat that price!Not everything in amazon is cheap make some research and calculation before ordering!

I would say this a medium quality copy paper with a very affordable price attached to it.  There is higher quality paper out there but you definitely will pay for it.  Guess it mostly depends on your personal needs.  I have a HP Deskjet F4400 printer and this paper runs smoothly thru it, does not jam and the paper does not stick together.  The print is clear and this paper works fine for my limited needs.

The wrapper was opened on one side when it got to me but luckily the damage was minimal with a bit of wavy edges. They need to pack these better. About 1-2$ savings over walmart if you get free shipping. Paper quality is just as good.Great deal for someone in school or prints a lot. Professional businesses that give handouts may want fancier quality.

I was disappointed with this paper and expected better from the Amazon brand which is usually very good.  This paper is too thin and too gray.  It doesn't seem like 20-lb weight to me.  I want a little more weight, even for everyday use.  Whether or not it's actually 20-lb weight, it's definitely not bright white.  It is a dingy gray and you can see it's off-white even without comparing it side-by-side with truly white paper.  I will use this pack of paper (only for unimportant stuff), but I won't buy it again.

I was buying from Quill, but they are so expensive & this paper is great quality. The only thing that sucks is they make USPS deliver it which I think is so rude that they have to carry & handle these heavy boxes. Should be delivered through UPS, but otherwise a great product

I was worried at first about this purchase, as I have bought off brand paper before and had horrible experiences. But I have not had any problems or issues with this product. Great price for a family that uses a lot of paper for school and work projects.

Very standard, middle of the road quality. Paper is as expected. I've definitely come across much cheaper quality at low prices, so I'm pleased with this brand. Price may not be the cheapest I've ever seen, but was the cheapest I could find at the time.

GREAT product and show approval by re ordering.This is not the place for it, but...  This ONE ream of paper came packaged in a box 20"x16"x5" with NO packaging material. That poor little ream of paper moved around so much that the ream package was opened...  The outside of the box was A LITTLE crushed on one end and the tape was NOT "Prime" tape.  Is that because it was an "add on" item?
It's good paper and perfect for everyday use. It's cheaper than Quill (maybe a $1) which is where I used to buy my paper. But why not buy this.

The paper is fine. Printer takes it up and prints just fine and it’s a good value. My huge issue is how they ship it. I buy multiple 8 ream cases and each individual case comes its own shipping box. It’s completely wasteful and we’re then left with multiple shipping boxes in addition to the cases themselves. Amazon, you need to ship these things properly without being so wasteful.

THE ABSOLUTE WORST PAPER I HAVE BOUGHT IN THE LAST 15 YEARS.  STICKS TOGETHER  IN MULTI PAGE CLUMPS. ABSOLUTE GARBAGE.  I JUST PUT THE HALF CASE IN THE DUMPSTER.  YES , IT WAS THAT BAD. WONT MAKE THAT MISTAKE AGAINREPLACED WITH HAMMERMILL 24/92
Paper is very thin amd flimsy.. can see through it when you print on both sides.. even on draft setting

It's kind of on the thin side. Even when I use the "draft" setting on my printer (which uses less ink than the regular setting), the text printed on one side of the paper shows through the back, so double-sided printing doesn't look great. This paper is fine for printing stuff that isn't terribly important, or to which I don't intend to return more than once or twice. I won't buy it again.

Serves our purposes well. Presentation of text and graphics using an inkjet printer is as good as the more expensive paper we had used. Very pleased with lack of defects in individual sheets. No wrinkles or curled corners.Copies are sharp.
Box looks good, but all beams are broken. It seems they are damaged and returned items. So disappointed...

I love the price and fast shipping! This paper is very thin though. It tears pretty easily. But, overall I am satisfied. You get what you pay for and this printer paper does it's job, so I'm happy. But warning, don't just yank a stack out of the sleeve, you'll rip it.
Multiple sheets have splatter on them. Looks like someone spilled coffee on sporadic sheets. Very frustrating when printing collated projects when multiple sheets have this splatter on them.

Good quality paper. Nice tight grain. Feeds perfectly in my Brother L6300DW. Interestingly, it has a slightly blue cast to it. You would never notice it looking at a page, but when set next to basically every paper I have used in the past four years, it pops! It could also be said that this paper is so white it makes every other paper look yellowish and dingy. However you characterize it, this is a nice substitute for the Hammermill Great White (also 92 bright)

It's a big box of printer paper, 5 reams, 2,500 sheets, for less than the cost of 1,000 sheets elsewhere. Do a lot of printing? Want a lifetime supply for infrequent printer users?  Want a whole squadron of paper airplanes? You've come to the right place.

AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper is a paper used for typical office work and work at home.  The paper is bright white, and it is not glossy.  Back in the day, I encountered paper that was off-white, and where this resembled the paper used for printing newspapers.  But AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper does not in any way have a "cheap" feel to it.  I've tested this AmazonBasics paper using my HP LaserJet Pro M402n printer, which I bought from Amazon.com.  This paper does not get stuck in the printer, and it does not wrinkle or bunch up in the printer.  Although I've used this paper for only two months, I have not yet encountered a situation where I needed to open up the printer and pry out and remove stuck pieces of paper.  The documents that I've printed on this AmazonBasics paper include: ( 1 )  Copies of my "Artist's Statement," which I plan to distribute tomorrow during an exhibition of my landscape photographs; ( 2 )  Journal articles in immunology; ( 3 )  Patents and patent applications.  When I click on the "PRINT" button, my documents are reliably printed without any smudge marks.  Also, the gray tones are reproduced accurately on this AmazonBasics paper, in the situation where the document includes black and white images or color images.

If you are going to use this paper to “print / copy” on with any expectation of print quality beware of requirements. This recycle media would be well-suited for taking handwritten notes or children drawing with crayons. Would not recommend using theirs in a printer that cost more than $50. If so make sure to correct the settings in the control panel so the printer knows it is printing on recycled media. For instants, every printer has a recommended paper media. Sometimes several. In order to print on this you have to reduce the amount of ink shot onto the page. Or toner. Otherwise it will bleed through and quality will look very poor. Also allow a very long amount of drying time (10 min or longer) Unless you are in an extremely dry environment.

We have been buying Georgia Pacific or Hewlett-Packard brand 20 pound white printer paper from Amazon Prime. Those cost about $5/ream when you buy the 3 or 5 pack. This AmazonBasics paper is $4/ream. While it is also 20 pound paper, the finish is not as smooth and even as the GP or HP papers. You get what you pay for. For personal use, the cheaper paper is fine with us. Interestingly, the AmazonBasics paper is made in France, while the other 2 are made in the USA (if you care). AmazonBasics 10-pack comes in a big heavy box that does get beat up in shipping, but the paper inside seems to be OK.

I know if I buy it, I will prob. be happy with it, and if not, NO company has ever stood behind their products more than Amazon....hence why many of us have made Amazon the GIANT they have become... the earned it.This paper is a great all around paper and a good price point... there are heavier papers for special presentations, and there is junk paper for scrap printing....but at this price point, I will print with this paper 95% of the time.... Kudos to Amazon purchasing staff who is filling out the Amazon Basic lineup....

There are other weights of copy paper that it would not compare well with, but when you compare apples to apples it seems to be essentially the same. 20# multipurpose is our basic go-to paper for black-and-white copies. What can I say, it's paper. It's rated at 92 brightness and is true to color as far as I'm concerned. Unfortunately, there are some big problems with this paper.So what's the issue with this product? Well, for starters, it's a lot thinner than other brands. I typically use Hammermill or HP paper (occasionally Target) and those brands are nice and thick. The reams sold here on Amazon don't carry the same heft and just feel cheap. The second I opened up the first ream I could tell it was lackluster paper. For reference, it's like if you bought 3-ply toilet paper and got 1-ply instead.

I've worked in a lot of offices and engineering groups, and at home have about six printers, 3 lasers, and 4 inkjets.  I've used many types of copy print paper, and this is not as good as most.  It tends to slip in the machine, one from my color laser, and all three of my cheaper inkjet printers.  When it did print it was OK fair to good, the paper is bright and somewhat slick. I had tried to write on it with a ball and it skipped.  I have this trouble occasionally with slick papers, but most copy paper has the texture to write well.  Is this really 20# paper, I though it looked a bit lighter than my other 20# paper, but maybe it's the density.  It did perform pretty well in the photocopy mode for the color laser, but I had thought this was an all purpose type, so while it's good for photo colors, it is not as good as the special paper made for that.  I use a better quality for photo printing to recapture some old family portraits and such.  This is good, but the expensive stuff for that is better.  The price is decent, but for a few dollars more you can do better, not recommended.

This is okay basic copy paper. It consistently feeds through my color laser printer one sheet at a time without jamming. It is less bright and more transparent than my hammermill paper of the same weight, but it is also significantly cheaper. It is not ideal for double sided use because you see shadows from the other side through the paper. Color is not accurate, but not terrible. It takes laser ink well and text is crisp. It doesn't cause patchy ink spots and adhesion is good. It works for school work, one sided documents, and coloring pages for the kids. For professional applications i would spend a bit more to get better quality, but for day to day use when you are not trying to impress someone it's fine. The case of 8 reams arrived in good shape, 8 individually wrapped reams in a large bankers box type box.

I like the way this paper is packaged- the box is more manageable in size than the normal size box of copier paper. It will probably take us a year or more to go through all of it at home. I ordered it for home use and we just don't print much stuff at home anymore.It works okay in our printers. One printer is an HP Deskjet and the other is a Canon Inkwell. I did try some in the higher speed copier at work, and it did jam up there but at the slower speeds of the home office printers it worked just fine.

I found some of the other (negative) reviews interesting because they were for high volume situations and different printers, which apparently caused some compatibility/performance issues. I had never thought of the finish of a paper or how it might react to different printers.In my case, my review is positive because it works fine with my black and white laser printer and has enough thickness that I can print on both sides without any major issues. How it does with inkjets and in high volume cases? I can’t say, honestly. But as one of two students in a household with maybe 5-7 pages of printing a week total, this works fine and is a great value! If I have to make copies, I can do that at home and it doesn’t cost much and looks fine. Normal brightness, works fine, printer takes one sheet at a time without issues. (Thinner papers sometimes jam printers—this one seems to be ok!)

Amazon throws its hat in yet another ring, this time it's standard 92 copy paper. This 8-ream box nestles into the usual crowd of hammerhill, hp, staples and other brands, and there seems to be little to set it apart.  The print quality is similar to the Staples or Office Depot brands, the price is similar at present, and so on.It's not premium quality, and it's not premium price. I tend to take my chances and use "copy paper" like this in my home office printers rather than laser printer paper. It's cheaper and works fine, today's printers don't seem to get gunked up with lots of fine paper particles that ruin them.
