No surprises. I have bought paper in the past that has bunched up or gotten stuck in the paper feed. I had no such problems with this paper though.

I use a lot of paper and print a lot of items.  What I detest most is going to the supply store and having to lug home a case of paper.  It is heavy and cumbersome.  The best part of these purchase experience is that it is delivered and when the case comes you can open it and take two or three reams at a time into your home office and use them as needed.The quality of the paper is high and the colors come out true and good.  I have a laser jet printer and did some pictures with this paper and they were true and very excellent.

This AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper is a quality copy paper for its class and brightness. Its thickness is such that it works well for copying and printing. The paper is smooth rather than coarse. I have had no issues with the paper jamming while going through the duplex process. I have had no issues with the paper feeding properly. The paper has not curled on me or done anything for which I can make a negative remark. We have a family business and use a lot of paper so if there were problems with this paper, we would have experienced those problems. I can recommend this paper for printers, copiers and for any other normal use of copy paper.

I have a home office using a Canon MX870 printer.  AmazonBasics Multipurpose Copy Printer Paper when printing text, images, flyers, brochures, and making copies of documents using the scanner (B/W & Color).  In all uses, the printing was crisp with sharply defined edges, large sections of color didn't ripple, double-sided printing didn't bleed through, and most importantly the printer never jammed (with some other brands I've had 1-4 jams per ream and with this paper none so far).Since printers vary and I used this paper for home office use, not large business use, your results may vary.  But with the quality of the paper for my uses, it was above average.

I am really impressed with this basic 20 lb paper.  I compared it to another brand of 20 lb, 92 brightness multi-purpose paper that I have and I find the Amazon Basics brand is a consistent white throughout the page, while the other brand name paper has a spotty appearance.  Look at the picture I took with the two side by side (Amazon brand on the left).  They are both 20 lb and 92 brightness, yet the Amazon Basics looks noticeably better because of its consistency throughout the page.  I looked at more than these two sheets to make sure it wasn’t just a fluke, and all the Amazon sheets have the same white look consistent throughout the sheet, while the other name brand sheets are spotty.
Not all paper is the same, but this one is good enough!I compared feature to feature with GP Advantage Premium Bright 96 / 22 weight just for fun.

This is good, every day basic paper to use. It is only 20lb weight so thin, thinner than I usually use, but I'm ok with that since I mostly use it for Etsy invoices these days. If I want to do something on better paper, I can just switch it out.I had no problems with it printing in my Brother 8360CDW laser printer. I didn't experience any creasing or problems at all with it.  This carton of paper is a real bargain for basic printing of handouts, sales reciepts, etc.... If your business needs a more 'professional' paper then this isn't the paper for you.

This is the product that just caused our law firm to ban Amazon Basics. We had tried other products from this line, hoping to realize savings and having faith in Amazon's reputation. Most of these products have been disappointing but the paper is terrible. The biggest problem is that our commercial Ricoh printer just jams constantly with this paper. It would jam in 5-6 places at once, too. We've never had that problem before. There were repeated service calls. We were advised to try different paper. We did. Problem solved.The worst part: the next batch of paper was cheaper because of an Office Depot special. In fact, our policy is always to buy the cheapest possible paper because of the volume we use. Only Amazon screwed up the commercial printer/copier.

If you need to print stuff that is either disposable, or plain text, then this is really what you want. Works better with LaserJet in my opinion, but it prints well with that that level of printing on an inkjet without too much bleeding. Anything more sophisticated, and even color, you might want a higher quality paper. This case of paper gets you 8 reams of 500 sheets each that works out to about $4.50 a ream. Paper has gotten pricey these days, and comparatively, that's one of the best prices you will find at case prices.

I tried one of the new reams on a ~35 page document with colors and highlighting on my Epson Inkjet.  The print quality was attractive and high contrast.  I will note, but this could be due to how I loaded the printer, but some of the pages were slightly bent out of shape.  Unless other reviewers find the same result I would assume this is due to my own lack of care.  I was pleased with the brightness and contrast of the paper and find it in every way comparable to major name brands such as Hammermill and HP.

I'm using this paper with my two inkjet printers, and it works very well indeed. I print primarily b/w manuscript pages, with occasional color copies, and it's been fine for both. The paper is practically identical to the Staples brand multipurpose copy paper I'd been using, so it boils down to price and convenience. 8 reams of this Basics paper will last me a long time, and if the mail deliverer doesn't break her back hauling the heavy box, I'll probably order it again when I run out. Recommended.

I was super disappointed that the box of reams came totally broken in shipment... I like to keep paper boxes for storage and whatever... other than that - its copy paper. White. Paper-like. Works fine in my printer. The kid likes it to draw on. It papers as hard as paper can paper.

I typically use 20-pound, 96-bright multipurpose paper from Staples in an HP laser printer to print packing slips. It is suitable for my needs. Staples typically offers rebates, so I have to pay full price and then apply for the rebate, which is a pain.This paper from Amazon is only 92 bright, so it's not quite as white, but the difference is quite subtle. It won't matter for general printing. This is not a paper one uses for presentations or high quality printing, so it shouldn't be judged against such papers.

I usually buy Hammermill copy paper for the office but after the last batch (terrible quality!), I tried AmazonBasics. For roughly the same price, we received a much better copy paper and no issues. Yes, it is plain old copy paper but the brightness and copy quality comes out just fine. Presentation-wise, I took a point off...it is thin (20lb.) so I use 28 lb. paper instead if I need to preserve or make higher quality print-outs. Overall, it's a good value.

This isnt worth the cost at all. You can get a similar paper from other places. Just search in your favorite search engine. It's way too expensive when the same or somewhat better quality is available at multiple other places. Seller also seems to be adding delivery cost to the price of this substandard paper.

This box of printer/copy paper has a total of 5,000 sheets (10 reams). This is the ideal size for back-to-school teacher lists, supplying the household for the school year, and office use.The reams ship in one box, which is very heavy. The box weighs just over 50 pounds, and the carrier will label it as a two-person lift. Be prepared to wrangle it into the house (or just take the paper out in separate reams to get it in the house).

As many of the reviewers have already stated: It's paper. And it's perfectly good paper at a good price. Perhaps not the best choice for printing out an old-school résumé, but then--does anyone do that anymore, anyway?One qualifier which does not influence my rating, since it's not product-related: 10 reams of paper is pretty heavy, and it was shipped in the original carton from Amazon. It looked like it had taken a real beating en route, and one of the reams of paper had a minor crease mark in it all the way through. Not a problem, for us, as generic printer paper, but it may be something to consider.

Doesn't paper usually come in 10 ream boxes? This is an 8 ream box, so be sure to compare by the ream, not by the box. The paper is good standard quality printer paper with a bit of extra brightness somehow. It's not glossy photo paper, and it holds the ink just fine, but it is a bit shinier than some. Otherwise it's good quality bond paper for most purposes.

I use this product for personal use and occasionally I'll do some work for friends.  When I do some work for friends, or even strangers sometimes, I like whatever it is that I produce to be attractive and impressive.  I am happy that Amazon Basic paper has the quality that I need.

So I guess it is slightly brighter than standard white paper.

This paper is a wonderful quality especially for the low price. It is better than any of the store brands I have tried before. I don't print very often, so I don't buy paper that often. When I do, I tend to pick up nicer paper so it's suitable for a variety of uses, including printing school reports, resumes, recipes, photos, directions, etc. I've been very happy with the 24lb, 97 brightness paper from Hammermill. Its quality is excellent and I also think it's a good value at about $31 for 5 reams. I was down to my last ream and a half, so I decided to check out the AmazonBasics 20lb, 92 brightness paper. Unfortunately, it's not great.The first sign of trouble with the AmazonBasics paper was the packaging. The wrapping on three out of the five reams were torn on the side. When I unwrapped one of the reams to try out, the first 20-30 sheets were damaged/creased. My printer jammed on the very first test print; the only time my printer has jammed in over a year.

Disappointed that there's nothing to indicate this paper is made sustainably. It only costs a buck more to get another brand (Hammermill) that is certified by Forest Stewardship Council, and I like knowing I'm not funding clearcutting of old growth forests.

The AmazonBasics 92 paper is ok. The paper has decent quality but it's thin. No surprises there considering the weight but still. Print quality is fine as long as you use standard print quality. Again, I have always found Amazon to be extraordinarily good at packing.  My paper arrived loose in a larger box, with two other smaller items that I had purchased.  The paper wrapping around the ream is thin, and provides little protection to the paper inside.  Both ends of the paper wrapping had partially burst, and the corners of the ream were damaged.  This means that most of the 500 sheets in this ream will be dented or rippled, and would not be suitable for business use.

If you are not going to be highlighting 2 sided documents you will be fine but if you plan on doing highlighting, best to up the quality. I dropped it from my original 4 stars to 3

This paper should be left in the amazon's stockroom to use for a liner to boxes before shipment. Although I read the reviews, both positive and more negative prior to my purchase. It is too light-weight, no possibilities for class. More than one page comes out of my printer for just one copy. Then, I experienced a bigger paper jam today where I had to basically turn my printer up-side down to remove the paper jam. I am saving this paper for my grandchildren and their friends to draw on when they visit me. I will also use this paper to write my notes on that do not require printing. It is not even good for scanning. What a waste of money, now I will have to return to Staples to purchase their copy paper, I have been using for the past ten years.
